abstract: Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American trade deal.
snippet: Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American...
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — Mexico's deputy foreign minister, Jesus Seade, said on Saturday he sent a letter to the top U.S. trade official expressing surprise and concern over a labor enforcement provision proposed by a U.S. congressional committee in the new North American trade deal.
headline_main: Mexico Objects to Labor Enforcement Provision in North American Trade Deal
headline_print_headline: Mexico Objects to Labor Enforcement Provision in North American Trade Deal

abstract: The aide, John McEntee, had been dismissed in 2018 on the orders of the chief of staff at the time, John F. Kelly.
snippet: The aide, John McEntee, had been dismissed in 2018 on the orders of the chief of staff at the time, John F. Kelly.
lead_paragraph: A close aide to President Trump who was dismissed last year by the White House chief of staff at the time is expected to rejoin the West Wing, according to three people familiar with the move.

abstract: A House freshman from New Jersey who was planning to break with his party and vote against impeaching President Donald Trump will become a Republican, a GOP official said Saturday.
snippet: A House freshman from New Jersey who was planning to break with his party and vote against impeaching President Donald Trump will become a Republican, a GOP official said Saturday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A House freshman from New Jersey who was planning to break with his party and vote against impeaching President Donald Trump will become a Republican, a GOP official said Saturday.
headline_main: AP Source: NJ Dem Lawmaker Plans to Become a Republican
headline_print_headline: AP Source: NJ Dem Lawmaker Plans to Become a Republican

abstract: U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg released the names of his major fundraisers on Friday, bowing to growing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren and U.S. journalists to be more transparent in his campaign.
snippet: U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg released the names of his major fundraisers on Friday, bowing to growing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren and U.S. journalists to be more transparent in his campaign.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - U.S. Democratic presidential contender Pete Buttigieg released the names of his major fundraisers on Friday, bowing to growing pressure from rival Elizabeth Warren and U.S. journalists to be more transparent in his campaign.
headline_main: U.S. Presidential Candidate Buttigieg Releases List of Major Fundraisers
headline_print_headline: U.S. Presidential Candidate Buttigieg Releases List of Major Fundraisers

abstract: The freshman Democrat, who represents a New Jersey district where President Trump is popular, told aides he would announce his switch next week.

abstract: It’s not the offense, but rather one party’s rejection of reality.

lead_paragraph: Republicans argue that the present impeachment process is nothing like Watergate. At that time there was growing bipartisan alarm at President Richard Nixon’s conduct, while the impeachment votes on Friday in the House Judiciary Committee were strictly along party lines.

abstract: As much as the impeachment battle over President Trump echoes that of President Bill Clinton, a wildly different political landscape has contributed to some striking differences.
snippet: As much as the impeachment battle over President Trump echoes that of President Bill Clinton, a wildly different political landscape has contributed to some striking differences.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Even as the House Judiciary Committee  prepared to vote on articles of impeachment, Lindsey Graham was in a back room trying to cut a last-minute deal. If the president fully admitted what he had done, he could head off charges of high crimes and misdemeanors. Mr. Graham scribbled on a piece of paper what the president had to say.
